11 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to enhance
12 consumer protection in the event ticketing market by regulating the resale of
13 tickets through improved transparency and the prevention of predatory and
14 deceptive practices. The bill proposes to require entities that resell or facilitate
15 the resale of tickets to guarantee to each purchaser a full refund under certain
16 circumstances; to provide clear, itemized price details, including taxes and
17 fees; to prohibit selling tickets that a reseller does not own or have under
18 contract, unless the reseller provides notice to the purchaser in a clear and
19 conspicuous manner; and to prohibit the use of ticket purchasing software or
20 other methods to bypass online sales limits or other security measures. The
21 bill also proposes to require annual licensing for ticket resellers, require those
